ddfcf3f413-09-12 ddfcf3f4(S) Man Deep Creek / Main Wall FAddfcf3f4 ddfcf3f4I recieved this email from Tazmania. It came from a New York Jew named Polinski. The email detailed the inherent difficulty in assigning a YDS grade to a long traverse into an established route: It read in pertinent part:
" I have developed the following algorithm for assessing the cumulative difficulty for the linkup of two or more routes/boulder problems. The algorithm is as follows:

VL = [ ( Vi)/Vn] + Vn (R, C)
Where:
VL = Linkup grade
Vi = (V1 + V2 + Vn); Vx Vmax-3; Difficulty must be assessed on a Sherman (V) or Eubank (E) grading scale
R = Recovery factor (-0.5 R 0.5; -0.5 = no recovery, 0.5 = full recovery)
C = Crux influence factor (-0.5 C 0.5; -0.5 = opening moves, 0.5 = final moves)
In short, the Sinister Traverse into Naked man is 12d."
I will say for the record everything I have sent Polinski has down graded and claimed to have sent it in better style. He thinks he boulders harder than God and Jesus and claims he is the only climber in the world who never gets pumped. Which is why he forgot to enter 'pump factor' into his equation - which of course ups it one letter grade. I would note for the record when I graded this I did not use the Polinski algorithum. I did what I always do and that was figure out how many points I need to get into the top 100 ranking and then add one letter grade.		  ddfcf3f4
